'gross fixed capital formation' means all the resident producers' acquisitions, less disposals, of fixed assets during a given period and certain additions to the value of non-produced assets realised by the productive activity of producer or institutional units, as defined in Council Regulation (EC) No 2223/96
Council Regulation (EC) No 2223/96 of 25 June 1996 on the European system of national and regional accounts in the Community (OJ L 310, 30.11.1996, p. 1).
;

'fixed assets' means all tangible or intangible
                                    assets produced as outputs from processes of production that are themselves used
                                    repeatedly, or continuously, in processes of production for more than one year;

